c. Histros. A piratical people occupying the triangular- shaped peninsula at the head of the Adriatic. They were reduced by M. Minucius Rufus (Fabius’s magister equi- tum) and P. Scipio Asina, 13.C. 221, in a single campaign.

d. Illyrios. In various tribes this people occupied the whole east coast of the Adriatic. They had long been formidable as pirates, but the fall of the Epirot power left them without restraint.
